That is odd... 1st time I've ever seen this from a Sony camera. I am on Firmware .200 and there was also a recent camera update in the 'What's New' Sony app. I'd try a factory reset as a last resort if the other suggestions don't work. If all of these fail to resolve the issue then you might have just gotten a defective device that needs to be replaced.
@yubeie, what's 'all these issues' that you mention? My Z5C has been rock solid and flawless so far. Every type of device sold and from every manufacturer is going to have a few bad apples in the bunch. Samsung, LG, Apple, HTC ect. You name the manufacturer and there are defective units..
Also, if you ordered from Amazon then you have 30-days to return it. 30-days should be more than enough time to fully test the unit for defects and faults.
@SX75C, you say the unit gets hot. What are you doing when it gets hot? Early versions of the 810 processor had some heat issues. Look on your box and see what the SI # is. Also what ver # is listed?
